ons%20with%20half%20a%20dozen%20AT%26amp%3BT%20workers%20across%20the%20country%20this%20week%20indicate%20it%20hasn't%20been%20off%20to%20a%20smooth%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20Dallas-based%20telecom%20giant's%20Atlanta%20offices%2C%20AT%26amp%3BT%20employees%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20a%20lack%20of%20enough%20open%20desks%2C%20parking%20lots%20that%20quickly%20filled%20up%2C%20and%20a%20limited%20number%20of%20elevators%20is%20complicating%20the%20company's%20plan%20to%20phase%20out%20hybrid%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInternal%20documents%20obtained%20by%20BI%20suggest%20that%20AT%26amp%3BT%20is%20aware%20that%20its%20RTO%20mandate%20is%20asking%20more%20people%20to%20work%20on-site%20than%20the%20number%20of%20workstations%20it%20has%20at%20some%20of%20its%20offices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20internal%20FAQ%20that%20was%20updated%20last%20week%20said%20that%20employees%20in%20at%20least%20one%20division%20should%20expect%20workstations%20for%2070-80%25%20of%20those%20who%20are%20assigned%20to%20a%20particular%20location.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20reminder%2C%20employees%20should%20not%20leave%20personal%20items%2C%20make%20signage%2C%20or%20add%20name%20plates%20on%20desks%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20document%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20items%20will%20be%20removed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20AT%26amp%3BT%20did%20not%20provide%20immediate%20comment%20when%20contacted%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20document%20follows%20a%20memo%20last%20month%20from%20CTO%20Jeremy%20Legg%20sent%20to%20employees%20that%20said%20his%20AT%26amp%3BT%20Technology%20Services%20division%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fatt-5-day-office-return-construction-seating-details-cto-memo-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewill%20not%20offer%20one-for-one%20seating%20per%20employee%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20under%20the%20new%20RTO%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20employee%20at%20the%20Atlanta%20offices%20told%20BI%20on%20Monday%20that%20he%20arrived%20before%207%20a.m.%20to%20ensure%20he%20got%20a%20workspace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20Atlanta%20worker%20said%20he%20arrived%20before%206%20a.m.%20and%20that%20the%20available%20desks%20he%20saw%20had%20been%20filled%20by%20employees%20by%209%20a.m.%2C%20at%20which%20point%20some%20employees%20sat%20in%20the%20dining%20area%20or%20around%20conference%20tables.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20actually%20enjoyed%20coming%20to%20the%20office%20and%20even%20came%20four%20to%20five%20days%20a%20week%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20employee%20said.%20He%20said%20that%20he%20felt%20the%20working%20environment%20%26quot%3Bhas%20deteriorated%26quot%3B%20as%20more%20employees%20returned%20to%20the%20office%20since%20last%20year's%20three-days-in-office%20requirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20worker%20said%20AT%26amp%3BT%20employees%20have%20already%20been%20competing%20for%20space%20and%20sometimes%20speaking%20over%20one%20another%20while%20conducting%20simultaneous%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMicrosoft%20Teams%20meetings.%20The%20elimination%20of%20hybrid%20work%20is%20heightening%20those%20challenges%2C%20the%20employee%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20Atlanta%20workers%2C%20as%20well%20as%20employees%20at%20other%20offices%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20finding%20open%20parking%20in%20a%20timely%20manner%20has%20been%20a%20challenge%20for%20themselves%20and%20for%20colleagues%2C%20especially%20at%20offices%20that%20have%20been%20converted%20from%20less-dense%20cubicle%20setups%20to%20more%20tightly%20packed%20floor%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20communications%20sent%20to%20employees%2C%20AT%26amp%3BT%20has%20said%20it%20will%20continue%20to%20monitor%20workspace%20capacity%20and%20usage%20and%20will%20make%20adjustments%20accordingly.%20Legg's%20memo%20said%20that%20the%20company%20anticipates%20some%20percentage%20of%20workers%20to%20be%20out%20of%20the%20office%20each%20week%20due%20to%20sick%20days%2C%20work%20travel%2C%20vacation%2C%20or%20other%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20in%20Atlanta%20also%20reported%20seeing%20signs%20in%20front%20of%20the%20office's%20elevators%20(which%20they%20said%20have%20seen%20increasingly%20long%20wait%20times)%20with%20motivational%20quotes%20recommending%20they%20use%20nearby%20stairs%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20said%20the%20signs%20included%20phrases%20like%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20elevator%20to%20the%20top%20of%20the%20corporate%20ladder%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BThere%20will%20be%20challenges%2C%20but%20each%20step%20you%20take%20brings%20you%20closer%20to%20who%20you're%20meant%20to%20be.%20Take%20the%20stairs.%26quot%3B%20It%20wasn't%20clear%20exactly%20when%20the%20signs%20were%20placed%2C%20but%20the%20Atlanta%20employees%20said%20the%20signs%20were%20gone%20by%20Tuesday%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20Atlanta%20employees%20told%20BI%20that%20an%20additional%20elevator%20is%20planned%20to%20be%20installed%20at%20the%20location.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20more%20workers%20are%20slated%20to%20arrive%20this%20year%20under%20subsequent%20phases%20of%20the%20company's%20five-day%20RTO%20mandate.%20AT%26amp%3BT%20previously%20said%20different%20divisions%20are%20setting%20their%20own%20schedules%20according%20to%20their%20business%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAT%26amp%3BT's%20move%20away%20from%20hybrid%20work%20follows%20similar%20moves%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-requiring-return-to-office-rto-mandate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%2C%20Dell%2C%20and%20others%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20are%20requiring%20workers%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office%20for%20the%20entire%20workweek.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20there%20is%20great%20value%20in%20having%20people%20connecting%2C%20collaborating%2C%20and%20innovating%20together%20in%20an%20office%20setting%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20AT%26amp%3BT%20memo%2C%20which%20was%20distributed%20after%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%2