Ft.co%2FkUkrvu6YKY%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FkUkrvu6YKY%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Elon%20Musk%20(%40elonmusk)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Felonmusk%2Fstatus%2F1876657662068461657%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJanuary%207%2C%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EColeman%20told%20Asterisk%20that%20his%20team%20developed%20a%20few%20prototypes%20and%20settled%20on%20one%20that%20allowed%20users%20to%20submit%20notes%20that%20could%20show%20up%20on%20a%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20was%20that%20if%20the%20notes%20were%20reasonable%2C%20people%20who%20saw%20the%20post%20would%20just%20read%20the%20notes%20and%20could%20come%20to%20their%20own%20conclusion%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20January%202021%2C%20the%20company%20launched%20a%20pilot%20program%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-birdwatch-misinformation-moderate-tweets-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efeature%2C%20then%20called%20%26quot%3BBirdwatch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20just%20weeks%20after%20the%20January%206%20Capitol%20riot.%20On%20its%20first%20day%2C%20the%20pilot%20program%20had%20500%20contributors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColeman%20told%20the%20outlet%20that%20for%20the%20first%20year%20or%20so%20of%20the%20pilot%20program%20%E2%80%94%20which%20showed%20community%20notes%20not%20directly%20on%20users'%20posts%20but%20on%20a%20separate%20%26quot%3BBirdwatch%26quot%3B%20website%20%E2%80%94%20the%20product%20was%20very%20basic%2C%20but%20over%20time%2C%20it%20evolved%20and%20performed%20much%20better%20than%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Musk%20took%20over%20the%20platform%20in%202022%2C%20he%20expanded%20the%20program%20beyond%20the%20US%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmusk-renames-birdwatch-community-notes-touts-improving-accuracy-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erenamed%20it%20%26quot%3Bcommunity%20notes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20allowed%20more%20users%20to%20become%20contributors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20same%20time%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-twitter-layoffs-hit-trust-and-safety-workers-again-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisassembled%20Twitter's%20trust%20and%20safety%20team%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20undid%20many%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterview-how-extremists-benefit-from-less-content-moderation-on-twitter-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplatform's%20safety%20policies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-is-removing-less-hate-speech-eu-criticises-social-media-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elowered%20the%20guardrails%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20content%20moderation.%20Musk%20said%20in%202022%20that%20the%20community%20notes%20tool%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmusk-renames-birdwatch-community-notes-touts-improving-accuracy-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bincredible%20potential%20for%20improving%20information%20accuracy.%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20how%20many%20users%20participate%20in%20community%20notes%20contributors.%20It's%20one%20of%20the%20platform's%20main%20sources%20of%20content%20moderation.%20X%20didn't%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223553d156-3462-413b-a184-45a9aba861a0%5C%22%3EHow%20the%20community%20notes%20feature%20works%20on%20X%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20community%20notes%20feature%20is%20set%20to%20roll%20out%20on%20Meta's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstagram%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Facebook%2C%20and%20Threads%20platforms%20over%20the%20next%20few%20months%2C%20the%20company%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20shared%20with%20BI.%20Meta%20said%20the%20feature%20on%20its%20platforms%20would%20be%20similar%20to%20X's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20X%2C%20community%20notes%20act%20as%20a%20crowd-sourced%20way%20for%20users%20themselves%20to%20moderate%20content%20without%20the%20company%20directly%20overseeing%20that%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20select%20group%20of%20users%20who%20sign%20up%20as%20%26quot%3Bcontributors%26quot%3B%20can%20write%20a%20note%20adding%20context%20to%20any%20post%20that%20could%20be%20misleading%20or%20contain%20misinformation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20other%20contributors%20can%20rate%20that%20note%20as%20helpful%20or%20not.%20Once%20enough%20contributors%20from%20different%20points%20of%20view%20vote%20on%20the%20note%20as%20helpful%2C%20then%20a%20public%20note%20gets%20added%20underneath%20the%20post%20in%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20here's%20an%20example%20of%20a%20community%20note%20attached%20to%20a%20recent%20X%20post%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EJanuary%20moment%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F92nRy2eiW0%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2F92nRy2eiW0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Just%20Posting%20Ls%20(%40MomsPostingLs)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FMomsPostingLs%2Fstatus%2F1876463819507261658%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJanuary%207%2C%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EX%20has%20made%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcommunitynotes.x.com%2Fguide%2Fen%2Fabout%2Fintroduction%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomplex%20ranking%20algorithm%3C%2Fa%3E%20behind%20the%20feature%20transparent%20and%20open-source%2C%20and%20users%20can%20view%20it%20online%20and%20download%20the%20latest%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhelp.x.com%2Fen%2Fusing-x%2Fcommunity-notes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX%20says%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20community%20notes%20%26quot%3Bdo%20not%20represent%20X's%20viewpoint%20and%20cannot%20be%20edited%20or%20modified%20by%20our%20teams%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20a%20community-flagged%20post%20is%20only%20removed%20if%20it%20violates%20X's%20rules%2C%20terms%20of%20service%2C%20or%20privacy%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilar%20to%20X%2C%20Meta%20said%20its%20community%20notes%20will%20be%20written%20and%20rated%20by%20contributing%20users.%20It%20said%20the%20company%20will%20not%20write%20notes%20or%20decide%20which%20ones%20show%20up.%20Also%20like%20X%2C%20Meta%20said%20that%20its%20community%20notes%20%26quot%3Bwill%20require%20agreement%20between%20people%20with%20a%20range%20of%20perspectives%20to%20help%20prevent%20biased%20ratings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFacebook%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Instagram%2C%20and%20Threads%20users%20can%20sign%20up%20now%20to%20be%20among%20the%20first%20contributors%20to%20the%20new%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20we%20make%20the%20transition%2C%20we%20will%20get%20rid%20of%20our%20fact-checking%20control%2C%20stop%20demoting%20fact-checked%20content%20and%2C%20instead%20of%20overlaying%20full-screen%20interstitial%20warnings%20you%20have%20to%20click%20through%20before%20you%20can%20even%20see%20the%20post%2C%20we%20will%20use%20a%20much%20less%20obtrusive%20label%20indicating%20that%20there%20is%20additional%20information%20for%20those%20who%20want%20to%20see%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-joel-kaplan-trump-nick-clegg-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJoel%20Kaplan%2C%20Meta's%20chief%20global%20affairs%20officer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20in%20Tuesday's%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223bbd8501-50bf-4d12-89b3-c35e3f5351a2%5C%22%3EPotential%20pros%20and%20cons%20of%20community%20notes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20possible%20issue%20with%20the%20feature%20is%20that%20by%20the%20time%20a%20note%20gets%20added%20to%20a%20potentially%20misleading%20post%2C%20the%20post%20may%20have%20already%20been%20widely%20viewed%20%E2%80%94%20spreading%20misinformation%20before%20it%20can%20be%20tamped%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20issue%20is%20that%20for%20a%20note%20to%20be%20added%2C%20contributors%20from%20across%20the%20political%20spectrum%20need%20to%20agree%20that%20a%20post%20is%20problematic%20or%20misleading%2C%20and%20in%20today's%20polarized%20political%20environment%2C%20concurring%20on%20facts%20has%20sometimes%20become%20increasingly%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20possible%20advantage%20to%20the%20feature%2C%20though%2C%20is%20that%20the%20general%20public%20may%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20trust%20a%20consensus%20from%20their%20peers%20rather%20than%20an%20assessment%20handed%20down%20by%20a%20major%20corporation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaarten%20Schenk%2C%20cofounder%20and%20chief%20technology%20officer%20of%20Lead%20Stories%2C%20a%20fact-checking%20outlet%2C%20told%20the%20Poynter%20Institute%20that%20one%20benefit%20of%20X's%20community%20notes%20is%20that%20it%20doesn't%20use%20patronizing%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20avoids%20accusations%20or%20loaded%20language%20like%20'This%20is%20false%2C'%26quot%3B%20Schenk%20told%20Poynter.%20%26quot%3BThat%20feels%20very%20aggressive%20to%20a%20user.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.threads.net%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20data-text-post-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.threads.net%2F%40zuck%2Fpost%2FDEhgYx4JbEG%5C%22%20data-text-post-version%3D%5C%220%5C%22%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.threads.net%2F%40zuck%2Fpost%2FDEhgYx4JbEG%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20View%20on%20Threads%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20community%20notes%20can%20help%20combat%20misinformation%20in%20some%20ways.%20For%20example%2C%20researchers%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20San%20Diego's%20Qualcomm%20Institute%20found%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftoday.ucsd.edu%2Fstory%2Fstudy-finds-xs-formerly-twitters-community-notes-provide-accurate-credible-answers-to-vaccine-misinformation%23%3A~%3Atext%3DA%2520new%2520study%2520published%2520in%2Cvaccines%2520with%2520accurate%252C%2520credible%2520responses.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApril%202024%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20X%20feature%20helped%20offset%20false%20health%20information%20in%20posts%20related%20to%20COVID-19.%20They%20also%20helped%20add%20accurate%20context.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20announcing%20the%20move%2C%20Zuckerberg%20said%20Meta's%20past%20content%20moderation%20practices%20have%20resulted%20in%20%26quot%3Btoo%20many%20mistakes%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Btoo%20much%20censorship.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20the%20new%20feature%20will%20prioritize%20free%20speech%20and%20help%20restore%20free%20expression%20on%20Meta's%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20President-elect%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Musk%20have%20championed%20the%20cause%20of%20free%20speech%20online%2C%20railed%20against%20content%20moderation%20as%20politically%20biased%20censorship%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-donald-trump-moderation-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecriticized%20Zuckerberg%20for%20his%20role%20overseeing%20the%20public%20square%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20key%20person%20appeared%20pleased%20with%20the%20change%3A%20Trump%20said%20Tuesday%20that%20%3Ca%20h