2%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20hidden%20middlemen%20who%20cost%20homebuyers%20%2412%20billion%20and%20counting%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20house%20exterior%20with%20a%20large%20price%20tag%20attached%2C%20and%20a%20hand%20holding%20a%20marker%20adding%20a%20dollar%20sign%20to%20the%20tag%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F677d5458f83fcec7e5b4db2b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20path%20to%20homeownership%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbad-real-estate-agents-realtors-homebuyers-sellers-housing-market-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elined%20with%20middlemen%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Real-estate%20agents%2C%20mortgage%20brokers%2C%20attorneys%20%E2%80%94%20all%20help%20push%20a%20deal%20through%20and%20then%20claim%20a%20fee%20when%20the%20ink%20dries.%20Most%20buyers%20are%20aware%20of%20these%20parties%2C%20but%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eone%20group%20mostly%20flies%20under%20the%20radar.%20Their%20fees%20are%20often%20hidden%2C%20lumped%20in%20with%20other%20charges%20or%20buried%20in%20paperwork.%20If%20you%20bought%20a%20home%20in%20the%20past%20decade%20or%20so%2C%20there's%20a%20decent%20chance%20you%20unknowingly%20paid%20hundreds%20of%20dollars%20for%20their%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20appraisal%20management%20companies%2C%20little-known%20players%20that%20have%20flourished%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-widespread-mortgage-fraud-toppled-the-housing-bubble-2010-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaftermath%20of%20the%202008%20housing%20crash%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20job%20of%20an%20AMC%20is%20fairly%20straightforward%3A%20When%20someone%20wants%20to%20get%20a%20mortgage%20for%20a%20house%2C%20the%20lender%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwhat-is-home-appraisal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorder%20an%20appraisal%20of%20the%20property%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20determine%20how%20much%20it's%20worth%20(and%2C%20by%20extension%2C%20how%20much%20they're%20willing%20to%20lend).%20But%20the%20bank%20or%20credit%20union%20typically%20won't%20hire%20an%20appraiser%20directly%3B%20they'll%20enlist%20an%20AMC%20to%20manage%20the%20process.%20The%20lender%20pays%20an%20agreed-upon%20sum%20to%20the%20AMC%2C%20which%20uses%20a%20chunk%20of%20that%20money%20to%20pay%20the%20appraiser%20and%20keeps%20the%20rest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AMC%20is%20basically%20a%20transaction%20coordinator%20that%20matches%20the%20bank%20with%20an%20appraiser%2C%20ensuring%20independence%20so%20that%20lenders%20don't%20pressure%20appraisers%20to%20contort%20their%20valuations.%20In%20many%20instances%2C%20however%2C%20the%20AMC's%20haul%20from%20an%20appraisal%20can%20match%20or%20exceed%20the%20amount%20paid%20to%20the%20person%20actually%20determining%20the%20value%20of%20the%20home.%20Most%20buyers%20will%20never%20realize%20this%2C%20since%20the%20AMC%20and%20appraisers'%20costs%20are%20often%20lumped%20together%20under%20an%20innocuous%20title%20like%20%26quot%3Bappraisal%20fee%26quot%3B%20on%20closing%20paperwork.%20Appraiser%20groups%20complain%20that%20AMCs%20don't%20even%20solve%20the%20problem%20they're%20supposed%20to%20address%20%E2%80%94%20the%20middlemen%2C%20they%20say%2C%20are%20incentivized%20to%20find%20the%20cheapest%20appraiser%20so%20they%20can%20pocket%20more%20money%2C%20resulting%20in%20shoddy%20appraisals%20and%20a%20bad%20look%20for%20the%20industry.%20All%20those%20fees%20from%20millions%20of%20home%20transactions%20each%20year%20add%20up%3A%20Data%20on%20the%20industry%20is%20scarce%2C%20but%20an%20analysis%20of%20public%20filings%20from%20one%20of%20the%20country's%20largest%20AMCs%20suggests%20these%20companies%20charged%20consumers%20about%20%2412%20billion%20in%20a%20recent%20five-year%20span.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20consumer%20advocates%20consider%20opaque%20appraisal%20fees%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%20most%20egregious%20examples%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-junk-fees-home-buying-house-prices-more-expensive-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehidden%20costs%20in%20homebuying%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20buyers%20face%20a%20rise%20in%20closing%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftitle-insurance-scam-mortgage-homebuying-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epesky%20fees%2C%20like%20title%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20pile%20up%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20transaction%20and%20usually%20total%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20%E2%80%94%20AMCs%20are%20attracting%20more%20scrutiny.%20The%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%2C%20as%20part%20of%20its%20crusade%20against%20junk%20fees%2C%20announced%20over%20the%20summer%20that%20it%20would%20look%20into%20various%20mortgage%20costs%20as%20well%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20growing%20power%20that%20appraisal%20management%20companies%20can%20wield%20over%20individual%20appraisal%20professionals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20appraisal%20is%20a%20notorious%20pain%20point%20in%20the%20home-sale%20process%3A%20A%20low%20valuation%20can%20sink%20a%20deal%2C%20since%20the%20buyer%20may%20have%20to%20pick%20up%20the%20difference%20between%20their%20mortgage%20amount%20and%20the%20sum%20they've%20offered%20to%20the%20seller.%20Both%20buyers%20and%20homeowners%20are%20known%20to%20gripe%20about%20appraisals%20they%20see%20as%20faulty%2C%20delayed%2C%20or%20needlessly%20expensive%2C%20but%20few%20are%20aware%20of%20appraisal%20management%20companies'%20hand%20in%20the%20process.%20AMCs%20are%20unlikely%20to%20go%20away%20anytime%20soon%2C%20but%20people%20familiar%20with%20appraisals%20tell%20me%20consumers%20should%20at%20least%20know%20exactly%20what%20they're%20paying%20for%20%E2%80%94%20and%20have%20the%20chance%20to%20push%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20appraisal%20is%20a%20critical%20part%20of%20any%20home%20purchase%20or%20refinancing.%20Sound%20appraisals%20don't%20just%20protect%20lenders%20from%20risky%20loans%3B%20they%20may%20also%20prevent%20consumers%20from%20overpaying%20and%20ending%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmortgage-rates-seriously-underwater-home-prices-south-midwest-housing-market-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunderwater%20on%20their%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20more%20left%20on%20the%20loan%20than%20the%20house%20is%20worth.%20A%20typical%20valuation%2C%20which%20a%202023%20survey%20by%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors%20found%20tends%20to%20cost%20a%20lender%20about%20%24500%2C%20is%20based%20on%20a%20physical%20inspection%20of%20the%20property%20and%20research%20on%20comparable%20sales%20in%20the%20area.%20Those%20fees%20are%20typically%20passed%20directly%20to%20the%20borrower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAMCs%20have%20been%20around%20for%20decades%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20until%202009%20that%20they%20gained%20prominence.%20Before%20the%20financial%20crisis%2C%20lenders%20mostly%20worked%20with%20in-house%20appraisers%20or%20contracted%20directly%20with%20independent%20professionals%20to%20carry%20out%20the%20job.%20These%20cozy%20relationships%20offered%20ample%20room%20for%20fraud.%20Low%20appraisals%20were%20undesirable%20to%20a%20lender%2C%20because%20a%20borrower%20might%20not%20have%20the%20money%20to%20cover%20the%20gap%20between%20their%20offer%20and%20the%20mortgage%20amount.%20To%20avoid%20losing%20out%20on%20a%20deal%2C%20lenders%20pressured%20appraisers%20to%20deliver%20the%20goods%20(and%20blackballed%20the%20ones%20who%20refused).%20Both%20sides%20worked%20to%20pump%20up%20home%20values%20and%20keep%20the%20good%20times%20rolling%20%E2%80%94%20until%20the%20entire%20facade%20collapsed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20web%20of%20new%20regulations%20%E2%80%94%20first%20through%20the%20Home%20Valuation%20Code%20of%20Conduct%2C%20then%20the%20Dodd-Frank%20Act%20%E2%80%94%20aimed%20to%20create%20some%20distance%20between%20lenders%20and%20appraisers.%20A%20lender%20could%20still%20technically%20manage%20appraisals%20in-house%20under%20the%20new%20rules%2C%20provided%20they%20separated%20the%20two%20sides%20of%20the%20business.%20Most%20decided%20it%20would%20be%20easier%20and%20cheaper%20to%20outsource%20the%20whole%20process%20to%20an%20AMC.%20Mark%20Schiffman%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Real%20Estate%20Valuation%20Advocacy%20Association%2C%20the%20leading%20trade%20association%20for%20AMCs%2C%20estimates%20that%20200%20to%20300%20AMCs%20handle%2070%25%20to%2075%25%20of%20appraisals%20ordered%20by%20lenders%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAMCs%20start%20by%20billing%20the%20lender%20a%20lump%20sum%2C%20which%20includes%20the%20amount%20they'll%20eventually%20pay%20the%20appraiser.%20The%20total%20fee%20for%20a%20simple%20single-family%20home%20could%20be%20about%20%24500%2C%20while%20a%20more%20complicated%20job%20could%20run%20more%20than%20%241%2C000.%20The%20lender%20gets%20to%20select%20the%20services%20it%20wants%20the%20AMC%20to%20provide.%20The%20AMC%20will%20then%20send%20the%20requirements%20to%20its%20network%20of%20qualified%20appraisers%2C%20who%20submit%20bids%20for%20the%20work.%20The%20AMC%20chooses%20an%20appraiser%2C%20checks%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20appraisal%2C%20and%20then%20submits%20the%20report%20to%20the%20lender.%20The%20burden%20of%20paying%20for%20all%20of%20this%2C%20though%2C%20ultimately%20falls%20on%20the%20buyer%2C%20who%20foots%20the%20bill%20alongside%20their%20other%20closing%20costs%2C%20detailed%20in%20paperwork%20before%20a%20sale%20or%20refinancing%20wraps%20up.%20In%20some%20states%20the%20lender%20is%20required%20to%20separate%20the%20appraiser's%20fee%20from%20the%20total%20amount%20billed%20by%20the%20AMC%2C%20but%20it%20often%20appears%20as%20a%20single%20%26quot%3Bappraisal%20fee.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%20ways%20for%20a%20buyer%20to%20deduce%20the%20AMC's%20cut%20%E2%80%94%20the%20appraisal%20report%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20might%20include%20an%20invoice%20that%20shows%20exactly%20how%20much%20the%20appraiser%20made%20from%20the%20job%2C%20which%20could%20then%20be%20subtracted%20from%20the%20total%20appraisal%20fee.%20But%20appraisers%20tell%20me%20AMCs%20often%20discourage%20them%20from%20including%20an%20invoice%20for%20fear%20of%20confusing%20the%20buyer%20with%20two%20numbers%20%E2%80%94%20I%20saw%20one%20order%20from%20an%20AMC%20that%20specifically%20told%20the%20appraiser%20%3Cem%3Enot%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20include%20an%20invoice%20in%20their%20report.%20The%20typical%20consumer%20probably%20wouldn't%20know%20to%20look%20for%20a%20difference%20anyway.%20Pretty%20much%20everyone%20I%20talked%20to%20for%20this%20story%20agreed%20that%20hardly%20anyone%20outside%20the%20appraisal%20world%20knows%20of%20AMCs.%20A%20buyer%20sees%20a%20bill%20for%20%24600%20or%20%24700%20and%20assumes%20all%20that%20money%20goes%20to%20the%20guy%20who%20crunched%20some%20numbers%20and%20nosed%20around%20their%20house%20for%20a%20few%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJosh%20Tucker%2C%20an%20appraisal%20manager%20at%20a%20bank%20in%20Texas%2C%20has%20spent%20the%20past%20two%20years%20gathering%20evidence%20of%20the%20fee%20imbalance%20through%20a%20nonprofit%20he%20cofounded%20known%20as%20the%20Appraisal%20Regulation%20Compliance%20Council%2C%20which%20aims%20to%20root%20out%20fraud%20in%20appraisals.%20His%20organization%20has%20collected%20hundreds%20of%20examples%20of%20appraisal%20orders%20from%20some%20of%20the%20largest%20AMCs%20%E2%80%94%20Class%20Valuation%2C%20Clear%20Capital%2C%20Solidifi%2C%20and%20Nations%20Valuation%20Services%2C%20among%20others%20%E2%80%94%20and%20compared%20them%20with%20the%20standard%20fee%20schedules%20the%20AMCs%20provide%20to%20lenders.%20Other%20internal%20documents%20show%20the%20appraiser's%20fee%20alongside%20the%20AMC's%20fee.%20In%20many%20instances%20the%20AMC's%20cut%20roughly%20matches%20or%20exceeds%20the%20amount%20paid%20to%20the%20appraiser.%20Take%2C%20for%20example%2C%20a%20single-family%20home%20in%20California%20that%20was%20up%20for%20refinancing.%20The%20appraisal%20was%20managed%20by%20Solidifi%2C%20a%20nationwide%20AMC%20based%20in%20Buffalo%2C%20New%20York%2C%20that%20says%20it%20handles%20about%20one%20in%20nine%20appraisals%20in%20the%20US.%20The%20appraiser's%20fee%20was%20listed%20as%20%24375%2C%20but%20the%20AMC%20fee%20was%20a%20whopping%20%24725%2C%20for%20a%20total%20cost%20of%20%241%2C100%20to%20the%20client.%20In%20another%20case%2C%20a%20townhome%20in%20Georgia%2C%20both%20Solidifi's%20and%20the%20appraiser's%20fees%20were%20about%20%24300.%20A%20Solidifi%20spokesperson%20tells%20me%20that%20appraisers%20generally%20receive%20the%20majority%20of%20appraisal%20fees%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20company%20provides%20fee%20transparency%20to%20the%20lender%20and%20the%20appraiser%20by%20disclosing%20the%20breakdown%20for%20every%20transaction.%20The%20spokesperson%20also%20says%20that%20the%20company%20follows%20all%20applicable%20state%20and%20federal%20regulations%2C%20including%20paying%20customary%20and%20reasonable%20fees%20to%20appraisers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETucker%20calls%20AMCs'%20charges%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20fees%20that%20is%20absolutely%20price%20gouging%20the%20consumer.%26quot%3B%20It's%20unclear%20how%20much%20AMCs%20rake%20in%20in%20total%2C%20but%20securities%20filings%20from%20Real%20Matters%2C%20the%20publicly%20traded%20parent%20company%20of%20Solidifi%2C%20offer%20an%20approximation.%20Each%20year%20the%20company%20estimates%20the%20%26quot%3Btotal%20addressable%20market%26quot%3B%20for%20AMC%20services%20in%20the%20US.%20In%20the%20five%20years%20from%202019%20through%202023%2C%20lenders%20ordered%20about%2028%20million%20appraisals%20for%20purchase%20and%20refinance%20mortgage%20originations.%20Real%20Matters%20multiplies%20that%20volume%20by%20Solidifi's%20average%20revenue%20per%20transaction%20to%20arrive%20at%20a%20dollar%20figure%20estimating%20how%20much%20Solidifi%20could%20bring%20in%20if%20it%20captured%20every%20single%20one%20of%20those%20transactions%3A%20%2416.4%20billion%20over%20those%20five%20years.%20Take%20into%20account%20the%20estimate%20that%20AMCs%20manage%20about%2075%25%20of%20appraisals%20and%20assume%20that%20Solidifi's%20fees%20are%20in%20line%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20industry%2C%20and%20it%20appears%20AMCs%20could%20have%20charged%20consumers%20about%20%2412.3%20billion%20in%20that%20period%2C%20or%20about%20%242.5%20billion%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20ballpark%20figure%2C%20since%20AMC%20fees%20vary%20by%20company%20and%20their%20revenue%20depends%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frevised-2025-mortgage-rate-forecast-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enumber%20of%20loans%20in%20a%20given%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20it%20may%20also%20be%20a%20conservative%20estimate%3B%20Real%20Matters%20says%20its%20estimate%20of%20appraisal%20volume%20is%20low%20because%20it%20doesn't%20include%20certain%20types%20of%20loans%20for%20which%20there%20isn't%20good%20data.%20Solidifi%20reports%20healthy%20margins%20on%20the%20appraisals%20it%20manages%3A%20After%20subtracting%20the%20payment%20to%20the%20appraiser%20and%20other%20%26quot%3Btransaction%20costs%2C%26quot%3B%20Solidifi%20keeps%20anywhere%20from%2022%25%20to%20almost%2028%25%20of%20the%20fees%20it%20charges%20lenders%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20year.%20And%20again%2C%20that%20fee%20is%20passed%20along%20to%20the%20borrower%20as%20part%20of%20closing%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchiffman%2C%20of%20the%20AMC%20industry%20group%20REVAA%2C%20says%20that%20cases%20in%20which%20the%20AMC's%20fee%20outweighs%20the%20appraiser's%20are%20rare%20and%20that%20AMCs%20have%20their%20own%20costs%20to%20bear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20more%20of%20an%20anomaly%20than%20anything%20else%2C%26quot%3B%20Schiffman%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BUsually%20it's%20about%20the%20same.%20Sometimes%20it's%20higher%2C%20sometimes%20it's%20way%20lower.%26quot%3B%20Chris%20Likens%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Nations%20Valuation%20Services%2C%20tells%20me%20his%20company's%20fees%20on%20a%20transaction%20never%20exceed%20the%20amount%20paid%20to%20the%20appraiser.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20instances%2C%20both%20Schiffman%20and%20Likens%20say%2C%20an%20AMC%20may%20actually%20end%20up%20losing%20money%20on%20an%20appraisal%20if%20it%20turns%20out%20to%20be%20more%20complicated%20than%20expected.%20Both%20also%20note%20that%20finding%20an%20appraiser%20isn't%20the%20only%20thing%20AMCs%20do%20%E2%80%94%20they%20provide%20quality%20control%20after%20the%20appraisal%20to%20protect%20both%20lenders%20and%20consumers%20from%20faulty%20valuations.%20However%2C%20a%202018%20working%20paper%20from%20the%20Federal%20Housing%20Finance%20Agency%20found%20that%20AMC%20and%20non-AMC%20appraisals%20%26quot%3Bshare%20a%20similar%20propensity%20for%20mistakes%26quot%3B%20and%20concluded%20there%20was%20%26quot%3Bno%20clear%20evidence%20of%20any%20systematic%20quality%20differences%20between%20appraisals%20associated%20and%20unassociated%20with%20AMCs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20solution%2C%20at%20least%2C%20seems%20pretty%20simple%3A%20Require%20lenders%20to%20make%20AMCs'%20fees%20clear%20to%20consumers.%20Have%20a%20line%20in%20the%20closing%20paperwork%20that%20shows%20what%20the%20AMC%20is%20making%20and%20another%20that%20shows%20what%20the%20appraiser%20billed.%20The%20website%20of%20one%20nationwide%20AMC%20advises%20mortgage%20lenders%20to%20check%20how%20their%20AMC's%20fees%20compare%20to%20the%20average%2C%20suggesting%20that%20%26quot%3Byour%20AMC%20should%20retain%20about%20%24100%20to%20%24125%20per%20appraisal%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20remainder%20going%20to%20the%20appraiser.%20Yet%20the%20Appraisal%20Regulation%20Compliance%20Council%20has%20collected%20hundreds%20of%20examples%20in%20which%20the%20AMC's%20cut%20well%20surpassed%20that%20figure.%20And%20if%20lenders%20benefit%20from%20knowing%20the%20exact%20split%2C%20it%20seems%20reasonable%20for%20the%20consumer%20%E2%80%94%20the%20person%20actually%20paying%20for%20all%20this%20%E2%80%94%20to%20also%20have%20the%20chance%20to%20decide%20whether%20they're%20getting%20a%20fair%20shake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20states%20already%20require%20the%20fees%20to%20be%20disclosed%20separately%20in%20closing%20documents%2C%20but%20there's%20no%20federal%20mandate%20in%20place.%20In%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%20over%20the%20summer%2C%20leaders%20of%20various%20appraisal%20industry%20associations%20argued%20that%20the%20agency%20has%20the%20ability%20to%20require%20this%20kind%20of%20disclosure%20under%20the%20Dodd-Frank%20Act.%20During%20a%20rulemaking%20session%20in%202013%2C%20the%20CFPB%20actually%20considered%20such%20a%20provision%20but%20ultimately%20decided%20against%20it.%20The%20CFPB%20concluded%20that%20requiring%20breakouts%20of%20the%20charges%20could%20%26quot%3Bproduce%20information%20overload%26quot%3B%20for%20consumers.%20The%20appraiser%20groups%20say%20that%20the%20decision%20was%20a%20mistake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20unused%20authority%20has%20allowed%20AMCs%20to%20abuse%20the%20conflation%20of%20where%20the%20singularly%20paid%20'appraisal%20fee'%20flows%20after%20the%20consumer%20provides%20payment%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20executives%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3Breaping%20significant%20financial%20benefits%20while%20harming%20consumers%20and%20lenders%20along%20the%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchiffman%20tells%20me%20REVAA%20isn't%20opposed%20to%20a%20disclosure%20requirement%2C%20though%20he%20argues%20it%20would%20be%20an%20additional%20administrative%20burden%20and%20could%20confuse%20the%20consumer.%20Tucker%2C%20though%2C%20says%20it%20shouldn't%20be%20prohibitively%20difficult.%20And%20consumers%2C%20he%20tells%20me%2C%20have%20a%20right%20to%20know%20where%20their%20money%20is%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20captured%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20Tucker%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhere%20these%20middlemen%20get%20to%20kind%20of%20do%20whatever%20they%20want.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjames-rodriguez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJames%20Rodriguez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20reporter%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20Discourse%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddlemen-homebuyers-appraisal-management-companies-expensive-hidden-fees-mortgage-loans-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736327222000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F677d5458257ced016c3a1e01%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddlemen-homebuyers-appraisal-management-companies-expensive-hidden-fees-mortgage-loans-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20you%20bought%20a%20home%20after%202009%2C%20your%20appraisal%20fee%20almost%20certainly%20included%20hundreds%20of%20dollars%20for%20a%20middleman%20you've%20likely%20never%20heard%20of.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jrodriguez%40insider.com%20(James%20Rodriguez)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddlemen-homebuyers-appraisal-management-companies-expensive-hidden-fees-mortgage-loans-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mark%20Zuckerberg%20unveils%20his%20latest%20persona%3A%20Elon%20Musk%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221744%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Zuck%20morp