Gone%3A%20Covid%20Keeps%20Killing%2C%20Five%20Years%20On%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFive%20years%20since%20Covid-19%20started%20upending%20the%20world%2C%20the%20virus%20is%20still%20infecting%20and%20killing%20people%20across%20the%20globe%20--%20though%20at%20far%20lower%20levels%20than%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20the%20current%20state%20of%20the%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Still%20with%20us'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAround%20777%20million%20Covid%20cases%20and%20more%20than%20seven%20million%20deaths%20have%20been%20officially%20recorded%20since%20the%20first%20infections%20emerged%20in%20December%202019%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20(WHO).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20true%20toll%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20far%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20also%20crippled%20health%20systems%2C%20crashed%20economies%20and%20sent%20the%20populations%20of%20many%20countries%20into%20lockdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20second%20half%20of%202022%2C%20infection%20and%20death%20rates%20tumbled%20due%20to%20growing%20immunity%20from%20vaccinations%20or%20prior%20infection.%20The%20virus%20also%20mutated%20to%20become%20less%20severe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202023%2C%20the%20WHO%20declared%20the%20emergency%20phase%20of%20the%20pandemic%20was%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20the%20virus%20seems%20to%20have%20gradually%20become%20endemic%2C%20according%20to%20experts%2C%20with%20occasional%20resurgences%20similar%20to%20the%20flu%20--%20although%20less%20seasonal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20also%20largely%20receded%20from%20the%20public%20eye.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20world%20wants%20to%20forget%20this%20pathogen%20that%20is%20still%20with%20us%2C%20and%20I%20think%20people%20want%20to%20put%20Covid%20in%20the%20past%20as%20if%20it's%20over%20--%20and%20in%20many%20respects%20pretend%20it%20didn't%20happen%20--%20because%20it%20has%20been%20so%20traumatic%2C%26quot%3B%20WHO%20pandemic%20preparedness%20director%20Maria%20Van%20Kerkhove%20said%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20October%20to%20November%20last%20year%2C%20there%20were%20more%20than%203%2C000%20deaths%20from%20Covid%20across%2027%20countries%2C%20according%20to%20the%20WHO.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%2095%20percent%20of%20official%20Covid%20deaths%20were%20recorded%20between%202020%20and%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVariants%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20Omicron%20variant%20emerged%20in%20November%202021%2C%20a%20succession%20of%20its%20subvariants%20have%20been%20replacing%20each%20other%20as%20the%20dominant%20strain%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20moment%2C%20the%20Omicron%20variant%20KP.3.1.1%20is%20the%20most%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rising%20XEC%20is%20the%20only%20%26quot%3Bvariant%20under%20monitoring%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20WHO%2C%20though%20the%20United%20Nations%20agency%20rates%20its%20global%20health%20risk%20as%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20the%20successive%20Omicron%20subvariants%20have%20been%20noticeably%20more%20severe%20than%20others%2C%20although%20some%20experts%20warn%20it%20is%20not%20out%20of%20the%20question%20that%20future%20strains%20could%20be%20more%20transmissible%20or%20deadly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVaccines%20and%20treatments%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVaccines%20were%20developed%20against%20Covid%20in%20record%20time%20and%20they%20proved%20a%20powerful%20weapon%20against%20the%20virus%2C%20with%20more%20than%2013.6%20billion%20doses%20administered%20worldwide%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%20rich%20countries%20bought%20up%20a%20large%20portion%20of%20the%20early%20doses%2C%20creating%20unequal%20distribution%20across%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBooster%20shots%20updated%20for%20the%20JN.1%20Omicron%20subvariant%20are%20still%20recommended%20in%20some%20nations%2C%20particularly%20for%20at-risk%20groups%20such%20as%20the%20elderly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20WHO%20has%20said%20most%20people%20--%20including%20the%20elderly%20--%20have%20not%20kept%20up%20with%20their%20booster%20shots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20among%20healthcare%20workers%2C%20the%20booster%20uptake%20rate%20was%20below%20one%20percent%20in%202024%2C%20according%20to%20the%20WHO.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELong%20Covid%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMillions%20of%20people%20have%20been%20affected%20by%20long%20Covid%2C%20a%20still%20little-understood%20condition%20that%20lasts%20months%20after%20the%20initial%20infection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommon%20symptoms%20include%20tiredness%2C%20brain%20fog%20and%20shortness%20of%20breath.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbout%20six%20percent%20of%20people%20infected%20by%20coronavirus%20develop%20long%20Covid%2C%20the%20WHO%20said%20last%20month%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20condition%20%26quot%3Bcontinues%20to%20pose%20a%20substantial%20burden%20on%20health%20systems%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20about%20long%20Covid%20remains%20unknown.%20There%20are%20no%20tests%20or%20treatments.%20Multiple%20Covid%20infections%20seem%20to%20increase%20the%20chance%20of%20getting%20the%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFuture%20pandemics%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20warned%20that%20another%20pandemic%20will%20strike%20sooner%20or%20later%2C%20urging%20the%20world%20to%20learn%20the%20lessons%20of%20Covid%20and%20prepare%20for%20next%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAttention%20has%20recently%20focussed%20on%20bird%20flu%20(H5N1)%2C%20particularly%20after%20the%20United%20States%20reported%20on%20Monday%20the%20first%20human%20death%20from%20the%20virus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20patient%20in%20Louisiana%20had%20underlying%20medical%20conditions%20and%20contracted%20H5N1%20after%20being%20exposed%20to%20infected%20birds%2C%20US%20health%20authorities%20said%2C%20emphasising%20there%20was%20no%20evidence%20of%20person-to-person%20transmission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20late%202021%2C%20the%20WHO's%20member%20states%20have%20been%20negotiating%20a%20world-first%20treaty%20on%20pandemic%20prevention%2C%20preparedness%20and%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20an%20agreement%20has%20remained%20elusive%20ahead%20of%20a%20May%20deadline%2C%20with%20a%20key%20faultline%20lying%20between%20Western%20nations%20and%20poorer%20countries%20wary%20of%20being%20sidelined%20when%20the%20next%20pandemic%20occurs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Covid%20pandemic%20also%20saw%20a%20massive%20increase%20in%20scepticism%20and%20misinformation%20about%20vaccines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20have%20warned%20about%20the%20prospect%20of%20having%20vaccine%20sceptic%20and%20conspiracy%20theorist%20Robert%20F.%20Kennedy%20Jr.%20--%20US%20President-elect%20Donald%20Trump's%20pick%20for%20health%20secretary%20--%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20US%20response%20to%20a%20possible%20pandemic%20threat%20over%20the%20next%20four%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736313840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Fc95a7sgo_covid19_625x300_07_September_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fforgotten-but-not-gone-covid-keeps-killing-five-years-on-7425284%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Around%20777%20million%20Covid%20cases%20and%20more%20than%20seven%20million%20deaths%20have%20been%20officially%20recorded%20since%20the%20first%20infections%20emerged%20in%20December%202019%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20(WHO).%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fforgotten-but-not-gone-covid-keeps-killing-five-years-on-7425284%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%